We want to write the products as functions of $x$ and $y$. My friend’s product, using direct substitution, is $(x-4)(2y-1) = 2xy-2x-4y+4$.
My numbers are $xy$. There is a difference of only a constant between the two products: \begin{align*} 2xy-2x-4y+4-xy &= 1\\ \Rightarrow 2xy-x-4y+4 &= 1\\ \Rightarrow xy-5 &= 1\\ \Rightarrow xy &= 6. \end{align*}
The answer is $6$.
